This directory contains some scripts for header maintenance.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
->header_cleaner.sh 
This script replaces the old headers by headers that make use of 'replacement tags'.
After trunk is converted to this new format, we should not need this anymore.


------------------------------------------------------------------------
->header replacement
This script replaces the 'replacement tags'. It should be run automatically by 
'make export'.

It uses the following files:

link_and_run.sh							#<-- do everything. run from this dir.
replace_headers.sh						#<-- replace all headers - specifies files
replace_header.sh						#<-- replace a single header - calls sed
replace_header.sed						#<-- the sed commands
Template_CONTRIBUTING_AUTHORS_END 		#<-- the template files
Template_CONTRIBUTING_AUTHORS_START
Template_HEADER

All of these files should be soft-linked in (or copied to) /src. Then running 
sh ./replace_headers.sh 
should do the trick. For convenience, 'link_and_run.sh' does exactly that.
